'''SMSS J031300.36-670839.3'''（简称'''SM0313'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-17938_105-57618634-1/astronomers-track-down-oldest-known-star-in-the-universe/ |title=Astronomers track down oldest known star in the universe |last=Kooser |first=Amanda |date=February 10, 2014 |website=[[CNET|CNET]] |publisher=CBS Interactive Inc. |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221222403/http://news.cnet.com/8301-17938_105-57618634-1/astronomers-track-down-oldest-known-star-in-the-universe/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>）是一颗位于[[银河系|银河系]]的恒星，距离[[地球|地球]]6000[[光年|光年]]。

==年齡==
SM0313的年龄约为136亿年，<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.smh.com.au/technology/sci-tech/new-star-found-by-anu-reserchers-may-lead-to-universal-truth-20140209-32ae2.html| title =New star found by ANU reserchers may lead to universal truth |publisher =''The Sydney Morning Herald''| author=Larissa Nicholson|date=9 Feb 2014<!-- UTC date for consistency, 10 February Australian time in the source -->|accessdate = 9 Feb 2014}}</ref> 是人类已知宇宙最老的恒星之一。<ref name="mit">{{cite web | url =http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2014/researchers-identify-one-of-the-earliest-stars-in-the-universe-0209.html | title =Researchers identify one of the earliest stars in the universe | publisher =Massachusetts Institute of Technology | date =February 9, 2014 | accessdate =9 Feb 2014 | archive-date =2014-02-14 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140214070609/http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2014/researchers-identify-one-of-the-earliest-stars-in-the-universe-0209.html | dead-url =no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20140210">{{cite news |last=Brainard |first=Curtis |title=The Archaeology of the Stars |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/11/science/space/the-archaeology-of-the-stars.html |date=February 10, 2014 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |archive-date=2014-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140211021013/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/11/science/space/the-archaeology-of-the-stars.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 恒星的铁元素含量上限非常低，不及太阳的百万分之一，<ref name=kel>{{cite web|url =http://theconversation.com/the-oldest-star-discovery-tells-much-about-the-early-universe-22944|title =The oldest star discovery tells much about the early universe|last =Stefan Keller|first =|date =10 February 2014|work =|publisher =The Conversation Media Group|accessdate =10 February 2014|archive-date =2014-02-21|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140221233254/http://theconversation.com/the-oldest-star-discovery-tells-much-about-the-early-universe-22944|dead-url =no}}</ref> 这意味着它是一颗[[金屬量#第二星族星|第二星族星]]，由最古老的的第一代恒星死亡释出的气体云聚集而成。<ref name="mit"/> SMSS J0313有较高的碳含量，是铁含量的1000倍。<ref name="mit"/> 除了形成于[[大爆炸|大爆炸]]的氢元素外，恒星还含有碳、镁和钙元素等，可能形成于低能量的超新星爆炸。<ref name=kel/>天文學家還從該恆星光譜的吸收線中發現了[[次甲基自由基|次甲基自由基]]（CH），並且未發現[[氧|氧]]和[[氮|氮]]。<ref name="nature"/>

==發現==
SMSS J031300.36-670839.3由[[澳大利亞國立大學|澳大利亞國立大學]]的天文学家使用位於澳洲[[新南威爾斯州|新南威爾斯州]]{{link-en|庫納巴拉班|Coonabarabran}}[[賽丁泉天文台|賽丁泉天文台]]的全自動[[光學望遠鏡|光學望遠鏡]]{{link-en|星圖家望遠鏡|SkyMapper}}发现，<ref name="NYT-20140210" /><ref name=kel/> 研究结果于2014年2月9日发表在《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》上。<ref name="nature">{{cite journal| url =http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/vaop/ncurrent/full/nature12990.html| title =A single low-energy, iron-poor supernova as the source of metals in the star SMSS J031300.36−670839.3| journal =Nature|publisher =''Nature''|arxiv=1402.1517|doi=10.1038/nature12990|date=9 Feb 2014| accessdate =10 Feb 2014| last1 =Keller| first1 =S. C.| last2 =Bessell| first2 =M. S.| last3 =Frebel| first3 =A.| last4 =Casey| first4 =A. R.| last5 =Asplund| first5 =M.| last6 =Jacobson| first6 =H. R.| last7 =Lind| first7 =K.| last8 =Norris| first8 =J. E.| last9 =Yong| first9 =D.| last10 =Heger| first10 =A.| last11 =Magic| first11 =Z.| last12 =Da Costa| first12 =G. S.| last13 =Schmidt| first13 =B. P.| last14 =Tisserand| first14 =P.}}</ref> SMSS J0313的发现意味着第一代恒星的超新星爆炸可能并不如之前想象中的猛烈。<ref name="mit"/>

